## Quick reference

### Orientation
1. Read [`.claude/project-init.md`](.claude/project-init.md) — workflow and coding standards
2. Read [`.claude/memory/MEMORY.md`](.claude/memory/MEMORY.md) — prior context index
3. Check open issues: `gh issue list`

### Issue & project tracking
- Tracking system: **GitHub Projects** (kanban board) + **GitHub Issues** (tickets)
- Create issues: `gh issue create` — use the right template (bug / feature / chore)
- Board cards move automatically via `board-automation.yml` — no manual updates needed
- Branch name: `<issue-number>-<kebab-slug>` (e.g. `42-add-auth`)
- PR title: `[#<issue>] Short description`
- PR body must include `Closes #<issue>` — auto-closes issue and moves board card to Done on merge
- Draft PRs are opened immediately when work starts, not when done

### Key rules
- One issue → one branch → one PR. No direct commits to `main`.
- Write failing tests before implementation (TDD).
- No secrets in code — use `os.environ` or `.env` (gitignored).
{{#if lint_command}}- `{{lint_command}}` must pass before closing a task.
{{/if}}- Prefer deterministic bash/python over LLM calls for hooks and scripts.
